org.dockbox.selene.api.keys

Class Key<K,A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dockbox.selene.api.keys.Key<K,A>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type parameter indicating the constraint for the type to apply to/retrieve from.
    A - The type parameter indicating the constraint for the value to be applied/retrieved.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RemovableKey

    public abstract class Key<K,A>
extends java.lang.Object
    A low-level type which can be used in combination with a KeyHolder to dynamically apply and retrieve values from types.

      • resolve

        public <T extends K> Key<T,A> resolve()
        Resolves the correct parent type for a given key, so it can be applied safely. This is useful when applying keys to supertypes which extend from multiple Keyholders. This method applies a constraint on the type, so that the supertype has to extend type parameter K, so we can ensure no ClassCastException will be thrown. This also prevents us from applying a Key made for type A to type B.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type parameter indicating the supertype to resolve
        Returns:
        The current instance, resolved for the supertype.
